ezer_df = car_df[pd.to_numeric(car_df['Model Year'], errors='coerce').notna()]
ezer_df['Model Year'] = ezer_df['Model Year'].astype(int)


ev_df = ezer_df[ezer_df["Electric Vehicle Type"] == "Battery Electric Vehicle (BEV)"]
hybrid_df = ezer_df[ezer_df["Electric Vehicle Type"] == "Plug-in Hybrid Electric Vehicle (PHEV)"]


popular_ev_make = ev_df.groupby("Model Year")["Make"].agg(lambda x: x.value_counts().idxmax()).reset_index()
popular_ev_make.columns = ["Model Year", "Most Popular Full Electric Brand"]

popular_hybrid_make = hybrid_df.groupby("Model Year")["Make"].agg(lambda x: x.value_counts().idxmax()).reset_index()
popular_hybrid_make.columns = ["Model Year", "Most Popular Hybrid Brand"]

popular_vehicles_by_year = pd.merge(popular_ev_make, popular_hybrid_make, on="Model Year", how="outer")

ezer_df = car_df.copy()
ezer_df.columns = ezer_df.columns.str.strip().str.lower()

geo_column = next((col for col in ezer_df.columns if 'state' in col or 'county' in col or 'region' in col), None)

if geo_column:
    ev_df = ezer_df[ezer_df["electric vehicle type"] == "Battery Electric Vehicle (BEV)"]
    hybrid_df = ezer_df[ezer_df["electric vehicle type"] == "Plug-in Hybrid Electric Vehicle (PHEV)"]

    ev_distribution = ev_df.groupby(geo_column).size().reset_index(name="Number of BEVs")
    hybrid_distribution = hybrid_df.groupby(geo_column).size().reset_index(name="Number of PHEVs")

    geo_distribution = pd.merge(ev_distribution, hybrid_distribution, on=geo_column, how="outer").fillna(0)

    geo_distribution["Total Vehicles"] = geo_distribution["Number of BEVs"] + geo_distribution["Number of PHEVs"]

    geo_distribution = geo_distribution[geo_distribution["Total Vehicles"] >= 5000]

    geo_distribution = geo_distribution.sort_values(by="Total Vehicles", ascending=False)

    geo_distribution.set_index(geo_column)[["Number of BEVs", "Number of PHEVs"]].plot(
        kind='bar', stacked=False, figsize=(16, 6), width=0.7, color=["blue", "green"]
    )

    plt.xlabel('Geographical Region')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Electric/Hybrid Vehicles')
    plt.title('Regions with at Least 5000 Electric Vehicles (Sorted by Total Count)')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right', fontsize=12)
    plt.legend(title="Vehicle Type", labels=["Battery Electric Vehicles", "Plug-in Hybrid Electric Vehicles"])
    plt.grid(axis='y', linestyle='--', alpha=0.7)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
else:
    print("No column describing geographical regions was found. Check available column names:", ezer_df.columns.tolist())

phev_df = car_df[car_df["Electric Vehicle Type"] == "Plug-in Hybrid Electric Vehicle (PHEV)"].copy()

label_encoder = LabelEncoder()
phev_df["CAFV Eligibility Encoded"] = label_encoder.fit_transform(phev_df["Clean Alternative Fuel Vehicle (CAFV) Eligibility"])

make_cafv_counts = phev_df.groupby("Make")["CAFV Eligibility Encoded"].sum()
make_total_counts = phev_df.groupby("Make")["CAFV Eligibility Encoded"].count()
make_avg_cafv = (make_cafv_counts / make_total_counts) * 100  #   100

make_avg_cafv_df = make_avg_cafv.reset_index()
make_avg_cafv_df.columns = ["Make", "CAFV Eligibility Percentage"]

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
plt.bar(make_avg_cafv_df["Make"], make_avg_cafv_df["CAFV Eligibility Percentage"])

for i, v in enumerate(make_avg_cafv_df["CAFV Eligibility Percentage"]):
    plt.text(i, v + 1, f"{v:.1f}%", ha="center", fontsize=10)

plt.xticks(rotation=90)
plt.xlabel("Make")
plt.ylabel("CAFV Eligibility (%)")
plt.title("CAFV Eligibility by Vehicle Make (Percentage)")

plt.show()
